text.section:
The office shall:
Enhance the quality of life for persons affected by dementia and for their caregivers;
Recommend the delivery of services in the most effective and efficient manner possible to facilitate the needs of people with dementia and their caregivers, after consultation with other agencies of state government that work with dementia-related illness;
Determine ways the Commonwealth may secure additional federal and private funding to provide additional services and programs through a coordinated effort;
Apply for any public or private funding relating to dementia that will enhance the office's abilities to perform its duties under this section;
Promote public and professional awareness and education of dementia and access to needed services and programs;
Oversee and receive reports from the Alzheimer's Disease and Related Disorders Advisory Council; and
Coordinate and oversee the implementation of the recommendations of the 1995 Governor's Task Force on Alzheimer's Disease and Related Disorders.
